## 9. Responsive Design & Mobile Strategy
 
### Philosophy
 
**Mobile-first, desktop-optimized.** Every component works on phones first, then progressively enhances. The mobile web experience is critical because many coin collectors will photograph a coin on their phone and want to submit immediately.
 
### Breakpoints
 
| Breakpoint | Min Width | Used For |
|:---|:---|:---|
| *(default)* | 0px | Mobile phones — single column, compact padding |
| `sm:` | 640px | Small tablets — padding bump |
| `md:` | 768px | **Primary breakpoint** — multi-column grids, desktop nav, form side-by-side |
| `lg:` | 1024px | Desktop — 3-column grids, sidebar layouts |
| `xl:` | 1280px | Large desktop — maximum content spread |
 
### Global Padding Strategy
 
```
px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8
```
 
All major sections constrained by `max-w-7xl mx-auto`.
 
### Navbar — Dual Navigation Model
 
**Desktop (`md:` and above):**
- Horizontal nav links inline (`hidden md:flex`)
- Auth state: "Login" / "Sign Up" buttons OR user avatar dropdown
- Active link: `text-brand-700 font-bold`, inactive: `text-neutral-600`
 
**Mobile (`< md:`):**
- Hamburger button (44×44px touch target)
- Slide-out panel: framer-motion from left, spring physics (`damping: 25, stiffness: 200`)
- Panel: 280px wide, full viewport height (`h-[100dvh]`), includes nav links + auth actions
- Backdrop: `bg-neutral-900/40 backdrop-blur-sm`, tap to dismiss
- Touch feedback: `active:scale-95` on hamburger, `active:scale-[0.98]` on nav links
 
### Key Responsive Patterns
 
| Component | Mobile | Desktop |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Coin submission form** | Single column stacked | `md:grid-cols-2` — photo left, details right |
| **Evaluation results** | Stacked accordion sections | `lg:grid-cols-3` — summary + details + expert card |
| **Showcase gallery** | Single column, full-width cards | `md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3` masonry-style |
| **Dashboard stats** | 2×2 grid | `md:grid-cols-4` row |
| **Pricing cards** | Stacked, full-width | `md:grid-cols-3` side-by-side |
| **Admin tables** | Horizontal scroll with sticky first column | Full-width responsive tables |
| **Coin photo** | Full-width with 16px padding | Centered, max 400px, dark display background |
 
### Touch Interaction Design
 
| Pattern | Implementation | Why |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Button press** | `active:scale-95` | Physical button depression feel |
| **Touch targets** | Minimum 44×44px (`w-11 h-11`) | Apple/Google guidelines |
| **Card tap** | `:hover` triggers on tap | Hover effects become tap-reveal on mobile |
| **Swipe** | Not implemented in v1 | Avoids conflicts with browser navigation |
| **Image zoom** | Pinch-to-zoom on coin photos | Critical for examining coin details |
 
### Responsive Typography
 
| Element | Mobile | Desktop | Breakpoint |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| Homepage h1 | `text-4xl` (48px) | `text-5xl` (60px) | `md:` |
| Page titles | `text-3xl` (38px) | `text-4xl` (48px) | `md:` |
| Body text & cards | No change (15px–20px) | Same | — |
 
> **Principle:** Only the largest display headings change size. Body text, card text, badges, and UI labels remain constant across devices.
 
