## 11. Authentication & Authorization
 
### Registration Flow
 
1. User submits email + password (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number)
2. Server creates User with `emailVerified: false`, generates `verifyToken` (crypto-random, 64 chars)
3. Server sends verification email with link: `https://mintmarks.in/verify-email?token={verifyToken}`
4. User clicks link → server validates token + expiry → sets `emailVerified: true`
5. User can now log in
 
### Login Flow
 
1. User submits email + password
2. Server validates credentials + checks `emailVerified: true`
3. Server returns: `{ accessToken (JWT, 15min), refreshToken (JWT, 7days) }`
4. Client stores tokens (httpOnly cookie for web, SecureStore for mobile)
5. All API requests include `Authorization: Bearer {accessToken}`
6. When access token expires, client hits `/auth/refresh` with refresh token
 
### JWT Payload
 
```typescript
interface JwtPayload {
  sub: string;      // User ID (UUID)
  email: string;
  role: Role;       // COLLECTOR | EXPERT | ADMIN
  iat: number;
  exp: number;
}
```
 
### Role-Based Access Control
 
| Resource | COLLECTOR | EXPERT | ADMIN |
|:---|:---|:---|:---|
| View own coins | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Submit coins | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Buy credits | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| View own evaluations | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| View assigned evaluations | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Submit evaluations | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Manage expert profile | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Assign experts | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Manage users | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Approve experts | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Manage showcase | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| View all coins | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| View all transactions | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Manage credit packs | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
 
### Middleware Pattern
 
```typescript
// Auth middleware chain — applied per route
authenticate       // Verifies JWT, attaches user to request
requireVerified    // Checks emailVerified === true
requireRole(...roles: Role[])  // Checks user.role is in allowed list
```
 
### Password Security
 
- Hashed with bcrypt (12 salt rounds)
- Password reset via email with time-limited token (1 hour expiry)
- Account lockout after 5 failed login attempts (15 minute cooldown)
- Refresh tokens stored hashed in database, revocable
 
