## 13. Coin Submission Flow
 
### User Journey
 
```
1. User clicks "Submit a Coin" → /submit-coin
2. Photo Upload step:
   - Drag & drop or file picker (web)
   - Camera capture or gallery (mobile)
   - Preview with crop/rotate
   - Max 10MB, accepted: jpg, png, webp
   - Photo uploaded to storage, URL saved to Coin record
3. Details Form step:
   - Title (required): "What do you call this coin?"
   - Metal (select): Gold, Silver, Copper, Bronze, Nickel, Other
   - Weight (number, optional): in grams
   - Diameter (number, optional): in millimeters
   - Year (text, optional): "1947" or "1800-1810" or "Unknown"
   - Country (searchable select, optional): ISO country list
   - Denomination (text, optional): "1 Rupee", "Half Crown"
   - Condition (select, optional): Good, Fine, Very Fine, Extremely Fine,
     About Uncirculated, Uncirculated
   - Your Notes (textarea, optional): free-form user description
4. Review step:
   - Summary card showing photo + all details
   - Edit buttons to go back to any field
5. Payment/Submit step:
   - If user has credits >= 1: "Use 1 credit" button → deduct → status = SUBMITTED
   - If user has 0 credits: show two options:
     a. "Buy credits" → redirect to /credits
     b. "Pay for this evaluation" → Razorpay single payment → on success → SUBMITTED
6. Confirmation:
   - "Your coin has been submitted!" success card
   - Status tracker showing: Submitted → Assigned → In Evaluation → Completed
   - "You'll be notified when an expert is assigned"
```
 
