## 16. Showcase & Public Gallery
 
### Three Display Modes
 
#### Mode 1: Full Evaluation (Public Gallery)
 
Admin-curated coins with complete evaluation visible to everyone. Purpose: demonstrate the depth and quality of expert evaluations.
 
**Card design:**
- Coin photo (hero, dark `bg-coin-display` background, `shadow-coin`)
- Coin title + era badge
- Expert name + credentials badge
- Full evaluation: origin, grade, rarity score, estimated value range
- Historical story (expandable accordion)
- Expert notes (expandable accordion)
 
#### Mode 2: Before/After
 
Side-by-side showing what the user submitted vs. what the expert found. Purpose: show the transformation value of the service.
 
**Card design:**
- Split layout: "What the collector saw" (left) vs "What our expert found" (right)
- Left: User's photo + their basic metadata (metal, weight, year)
- Right: Expert's full evaluation with grade, rarity, value, story
- CTA: "Get your coins evaluated →"
 
#### Mode 3: Teaser
 
Partial evaluation visible — enough to intrigue, not enough to satisfy. Purpose: convert visitors to paying users.
 
**Card design:**
- Coin photo (full, beautiful display)
- Grade badge + rarity score visible
- Value range and historical story **blurred/locked** with CSS `filter: blur(8px)` overlay
- Overlay: "Sign up to see full evaluations" with CTA button
- Lock icon on hidden fields
 
### Showcase Page Layout
 
- Hero: "The MintMarks Gallery" with subtitle — curated evaluations from around the world
- Filter bar: by era, region, metal, grade (pill/chip buttons)
- Grid: `md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8`
- Featured items: larger card spanning 2 columns (`md:col-span-2`)
