## 24. Security Checklist
 
Based on OWASP Top 10:
 
| # | Threat | Mitigation |
|:---|:---|:---|
| A01 | Broken Access Control | Role-based middleware on every endpoint. UUID IDs prevent enumeration. Users can only access own coins/evaluations. Ownership check in service layer. |
| A02 | Cryptographic Failures | bcrypt (12 rounds) for passwords. JWT signed with strong secret (256-bit). HTTPS enforced in production. Razorpay secrets never exposed to client. |
| A03 | Injection | Prisma ORM (parameterized queries by default). Zod input validation on all endpoints. No raw SQL queries anywhere. |
| A04 | Insecure Design | Rate limiting on auth endpoints (5 attempts/15 min). Email verification required before any paid action. CSRF protection on web forms. |
| A05 | Security Misconfiguration | Helmet.js for HTTP security headers. CORS whitelist (only known domains). Environment variables for all secrets (never in code or git). |
| A06 | Vulnerable Components | `npm audit` in CI pipeline. Dependabot or Renovate for dependency updates. Pin major versions. |
| A07 | Auth Failures | JWT expiry (15 min access, 7 day refresh). Refresh token rotation on use. Account lockout after 5 failed attempts. Password complexity enforcement. |
| A08 | Data Integrity | Razorpay webhook signature verification (HMAC SHA256). Payment verification on server only (never trust client). Input sanitization. |
| A09 | Logging Failures | Structured logging (winston/pino). Log auth events, payment events, admin actions, errors. No PII in logs (mask emails, never log passwords). |
| A10 | SSRF | No user-controlled URLs in server-side requests. Image upload validates file type via magic bytes (not just extension). Filenames are UUID-generated. |
 
### Additional Security Measures
 
- **File Upload Security:** Validate MIME type via magic bytes. Max 10MB. Only jpg/png/webp. Rename all files to UUID on storage. No user-controlled file paths.
- **Rate Limiting:** 100 req/min general, 5 req/15min for auth endpoints, 10 req/min for file uploads.
- **CORS:** Whitelist: `https://mintmarks.in`, `http://localhost:3000` (dev only), mobile app origin.
- **Content Security Policy:** Strict CSP headers via Helmet.js.
- **SQL Injection:** Impossible with Prisma ORM — all queries are parameterized.
 
