## 25. Deployment & DevOps
 
### Architecture-Agnostic Deployment
 
No vendor lock-in. The application runs on any infrastructure that supports Node.js + PostgreSQL.
 
| Component | Options | Notes |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **Website (Next.js)** | Vercel, AWS Amplify, Docker, any Node.js host | SSR + static generation |
| **API (Express)** | Railway, Render, AWS EC2/ECS, Docker, any Node.js host | Stateless, horizontally scalable |
| **Database (PostgreSQL)** | AWS RDS, Neon, Supabase (DB only), Railway, self-hosted | Managed preferred for automated backups |
| **Image Storage** | AWS S3, Cloudinary, Backblaze B2, local filesystem | Abstracted via storage interface — swap without code changes |
| **Mobile App** | Apple App Store + Google Play Store | Built via EAS Build (Expo Application Services) |
 
